# Four-option chooser (Cursor / Composer / Auto)

Substantive replies in this workspace end with **exactly four numbered next moves** (`1.` through `4.`), plain markdown, **mission-ranked**, concrete in the first clause. **Option 4** is the user-authorship slot (`4. Provide your own next move.` or equivalent).

Pure acknowledgments with **no** decision surface may omit the quad; default is four.

Authoritative copy: `CLAUDE.md` (**Choosers are control surfaces** for doctrine; **Skill routing** at file end for the full IDE clause). `AGENTS.md` **Skill routing** mirrors file-end **Skill routing**; its **IDE agents** paragraph **opens** by pointing to `CLAUDE.md` **Choosers are control surfaces** (wording discipline, cheap test, slot-4 user-authorship), then states the plain-markdown contract.
